## ============================================================================
## MyAddon.toc — Table of Contents
## ============================================================================
## This file tells WoW which Lua files to load and in what order.
## It also provides metadata displayed in the addon list.
##
## IMPORTANT: The ## Interface line MUST match the current game version.
## Addons with Interface below 120000 will NOT load in Midnight without
## the player manually enabling "Load out of date addons."
##
## Reference: https://warcraft.wiki.gg/wiki/TOC_format
## ============================================================================

## ---- Required Metadata ----
## Interface is the game version this addon targets.
## 120001 = Patch 12.0.1 (Midnight). Update this when new patches ship.
## You can list multiple versions: 120001, 110002, 40402
## Interface: 120001
## Title: MyAddon
## Notes: A starter addon built with the Midnight Addon Template.
## Author: YourName
## Version: @project-version@

## ---- SavedVariables ----
## These global Lua variable names are persisted across sessions.
## The client reads/writes them from WTF/Account/.../SavedVariables/MyAddon.lua
## They are NOT available until ADDON_LOADED fires for YOUR addon.
## SavedVariables: MyAddonDB
## Per-character saved data (uncomment if needed):
## SavedVariablesPerCharacter: MyAddonCharDB

## ---- Addon Compartment (Minimap Dropdown) ----
## Introduced in 10.1.0. Adds your addon to the minimap addon dropdown.
## Functions MUST be global (not local). Only AddonCompartmentFunc is required.
## AddonCompartmentFunc: MyAddon_OnCompartmentClick
## AddonCompartmentFuncOnEnter: MyAddon_OnCompartmentEnter
## AddonCompartmentFuncOnLeave: MyAddon_OnCompartmentLeave

## ---- Icon ----
## IconTexture is shown in the addon list and the Addon Compartment dropdown.
## Use a standard WoW icon path or a custom texture in your addon folder.
## IconTexture: Interface\AddOns\MyAddon\icon

## ---- Optional Dependencies ----
## These addons load BEFORE yours if present, but yours still loads if they're missing.
## List libraries and addons you integrate with.
## OptionalDeps: LibStub, CallbackHandler-1.0

## ---- Distribution Platform IDs ----
## These are used by BigWigsMods/packager to upload to the correct project.
## Get your IDs from each platform's project page.
## Replace with your real IDs when you create your projects.
## X-Curse-Project-ID: 0
## X-Wago-ID: CHANGEME
## X-WoWI-ID: 0

## ---- Category ----
## Category: Miscellaneous

## ---- Custom Metadata (Optional) ----
## You can define arbitrary X- fields for use in your addon code.
## Read them with C_AddOns.GetAddOnMetadata("MyAddon", "X-MyField")
## X-Category: Interface Enhancements

## ============================================================================
## File Load Order
## ============================================================================
## Files are loaded top-to-bottom, synchronously, before the game world appears.
## Each file receives (addonName, namespace) as its ... varargs.
##
## RULE: Libraries first, then init, then features, then config.
## This ensures the namespace is set up before feature code runs.
## ============================================================================

## ---- Libraries ----
## These lines are wrapped in @no-lib-strip@ so the BigWigs packager
## removes them in -nolib builds (where a shared lib addon provides them).
#@no-lib-strip@
Libs\LibStub\LibStub.lua
Libs\CallbackHandler-1.0\CallbackHandler-1.0.lua
#@end-no-lib-strip@

## ---- Addon Files ----
## Init.lua sets up the namespace and handles ADDON_LOADED/PLAYER_LOGIN.
## Core.lua contains the main feature logic.
## Config.lua registers the Settings panel.
Init.lua
Core.lua
Config.lua
